      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-credibility-claim",
      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "CFD hemolysis model meets MRL-5 credibility requirements for absolute VAD hemolysis prediction",
      "description": "The CFD model for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump has been assessed against all 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors at Model Risk Level 5. Seven factors were formally assessed; six were flagged as epistemic gaps. The model demonstrates sufficient predictive capability for absolute hemolysis index values across five operating conditions when combined with Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification. This claim asserts that the aggregate credibility evidence, including mesh convergence studies, experimental validation against PIV and hemolysis bench data, and software quality assurance records, collectively supports regulatory submission under the Class III VAD context of use.",
      "scope": "FDA generic centrifugal blood pump; 5 flow-speed operating points; absolute hemolysis index (NIH); Monte Carlo UQ ensemble of 500 samples; MRL 5 per Morrison 2021 framework"
    }
  ],
